The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, May 07, 2004 				 All the way from Tanjore
India prides herself on being one of the most culturally rich nations of the world. A significant contribution to this cultural wealth had its origins in 18th century Tanjore or Thanjavoor whose paintings are an amazing visual amalgamation of both art and craft. It draws its inspiration largely from mythology, prominent among which are the figures of Lord Krishna and Ganesha. Tanjore art has carved out a singular niche in the melting pot of Indian culture by virtue of a uniqueness that sets it apart; the rich embellishments in gold and three-dimensional effect born out of an impeccable relief work are what have cemented its place in an ever evolving Indian culture. 																								Event: An exhibition of Tanjore Art																								When: Till May 9; 11 am - 7 pm																								Where: 4 Dover Park, Calcutta 19
